# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Zyra Blog Studio — environment variables
#
# EVERY key below is OPTIONAL. With no keys set, the app runs entirely on
# realistic MOCK providers so you can demo the full workflow offline.
# A provider switches to LIVE automatically the moment its key(s) are present.
#
# NEVER commit a filled-in copy of this file. Put real values in `.env` (which
# is git-ignored). Do not paste secrets into chat or share them.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Writing model (LLM) — split by role ──────────────────────────────────────
# Zyra's choice: OpenAI (cheap) for grunt work, Claude Sonnet for the actual writing.
#
# CHEAP role  → OpenAI, used for query expansion, clustering, scoring assist,
#               and research summarisation. Set to the cheapest suitable model
#               (verify the current id/price on OpenAI's pricing page).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_MODEL_CHEAP=gpt-4o-mini
#
# WRITER role → Claude, used for the blog draft + human-edit polish (best prose).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
CLAUDE_MODEL_WRITER=claude-sonnet-5
#
# Hero-image generation reuses OPENAI_API_KEY (above). Model is configurable.
OPENAI_IMAGE_MODEL=gpt-image-1
#
# Role→provider wiring (defaults shown; change only to override the split above).
LLM_CHEAP_PROVIDER=openai
LLM_WRITER_PROVIDER=claude

# ── Keyword research — Google Ads (Keyword Planner) ──────────────────────────
# FREE with an active Google Ads account, BUT: returns bucketed volume RANGES
# and AD competition + CPC (NOT true SEO keyword difficulty), and requires an
# approved developer token + OAuth2 refresh token (one-time setup, can take days).
# See docs/API_RECOMMENDATIONS.md for the setup steps.
GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN=
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_ADS_REFRESH_TOKEN=
GOOGLE_ADS_CUSTOMER_ID=
GOOGLE_ADS_LOGIN_CUSTOMER_ID=

# ── SERP + People-Also-Ask + autocomplete — DataForSEO (primary) ─────────────
# Chosen for versatility + low pay-as-you-go cost (~$50 min top-up, no subscription).
# Handles Google SERP, PAA, related searches, autocomplete, and competitor SERPs.
DATAFORSEO_LOGIN=
DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD=
# SerpApi — optional swap-in if you prefer its parsing (verify current plan price).
SERPAPI_KEY=

# ── Reddit questions — Apify (Zyra's account) ────────────────────────────────
# Uses an Apify actor to pull Reddit threads/questions. Set your Apify API token.
# Optionally pin a specific actor id (defaults to a Reddit scraper actor in code).
APIFY_TOKEN=
APIFY_REDDIT_ACTOR=

# ── X questions — twitterapi.io ──────────────────────────────────────────────
TWITTERAPI_KEY=

# ── Publish to thezyra.in (opens a PR — never commits to the default branch) ──
# GitHub token with "repo" (or fine-grained Contents + Pull requests: write)
# access to the target repo. NEVER paste it in chat or commit it.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
# Target repo + branch + file (defaults shown — change only if they move).
PUBLISH_REPO=toolsatZyra/ZyraUpdated
PUBLISH_BASE_BRANCH=master
PUBLISH_BLOG_DATA_PATH=src/lib/blog-data.ts
